    <abstract id="aspace_8a08e2bacc575d20cefbffb0f99ea1fb">Montanna Houston was a writer, artist and musician who lived in New York City and later in Houston, Texas. This collection includes correspondence, collages and twelve-step program narratives written by  Houston. The correspondence is mostly addressed to William Mathers, and there is one letter from Wojnarowicz to Montanna.</abstract>
